<task id="006" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-06 Rename `IAnalysisToolHandler` → `IToolHandler` with Type Alias (Pillar 2)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>007, 008, 009</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, refactoring, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.cs` files across `Services/Ai/` ; interface rename impacts all existing handler implementations; tag `bff-api` + `refactoring`; downstream blocker.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent of Pillar 1 tasks; touches different files; safe to run alongside 001-005.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Rename `IAnalysisToolHandler` → `IToolHandler` to reflect its new cross-context use
    (playbook + chat). Preserve a `using IAnalysisToolHandler = IToolHandler` type alias
    for source compatibility, so existing handler implementations (`GenericAnalysisHandler`,
    `DocumentClassifierHandler`, `SummaryHandler`, `SemanticSearchToolHandler`) and any
    consumer code continue to compile without per-file edits.

    Critical-path context: this rename is the structural prerequisite for Pillar 2's
    cross-context tool registry. Tasks 007 (AvailableInContexts), 008 (JsonSchema), 009
    (execution context split), 010 (adapter), 011 (chat agent factory wiring), and 012
    (batch migration of 10 chat tools) all consume the renamed interface.

    Pattern: simple interface rename + add type alias for source-compat. All existing
    handlers + DI registrations remain functional. The interface contract itself does NOT
    change in this task; FR-07/08/09 (adding `AvailableInContexts`, `JsonSchema`,
    `ChatInvocationContext`) come in later tasks.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 refactoring experience and familiarity with the
    Spaarke `IAnalysisToolHandler` ecosystem.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `IAnalysisToolHandler` is renamed to `IToolHandler`; a `using` alias preserves source
    compatibility; all existing handlers + DI registrations continue to work; existing
    tests pass unchanged; build green. Publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

